00:47:42.838 --> 00:47:45.705
it's typical brilliant reasoning
where he just basically--

00:47:45.705 --> 00:47:47.830
he looked at the history
of the Earth and said, oh,

00:47:47.830 --> 00:47:50.163
look the Earth is only going
to be habitable for another

00:47:50.163 --> 00:47:51.480
billion or half--

00:47:51.480 --> 00:47:52.830
maybe a half billion years.

00:47:52.830 --> 00:47:55.100
And intelligence didn't show
up until the end, right?

00:47:55.100 --> 00:47:56.683
So therefore it must
be-- intelligence

00:47:56.683 --> 00:47:57.750
must be hard, right?

00:47:57.750 --> 00:47:58.560
And so then he came
up with this idea

00:47:58.560 --> 00:48:00.030
there must have been
a bunch of hard steps

00:48:00.030 --> 00:48:01.549
that evolution
had to go through.

00:48:01.549 --> 00:48:03.840
So from that he was able to
use the correct probability

00:48:03.840 --> 00:48:05.340
distributions, et cetera.

00:48:05.340 --> 00:48:08.670
And he estimated there
were 10 hard steps, right?

00:48:08.670 --> 00:48:11.760
And so then he calculated out of
that what that probability had

00:48:11.760 --> 00:48:12.780
to be there for.

00:48:12.780 --> 00:48:14.055
And he got 10 to the 20.

00:48:14.055 --> 00:48:15.930
And he concluded in
that-- there's actually--

00:48:15.930 --> 00:48:16.770
I put that quote in there.

00:48:16.770 --> 00:48:18.270
I'd have to switch
all the way back.

00:48:18.270 --> 00:48:20.751
But he basically said, based
on this 10 to the minus 20.

00:48:20.751 --> 00:48:21.250
Sorry.

00:48:21.250 --> 00:48:23.106
He said, based on this,
we are the only time

00:48:23.106 --> 00:48:24.480
that civilization
has ever formed

00:48:24.480 --> 00:48:25.650
in the history of the universe.

00:48:25.650 --> 00:48:27.047
Now you do the--
you've got data.

00:48:27.047 --> 00:48:27.630
You put it in.

00:48:27.630 --> 00:48:29.030
You find that no,
actually, in your model--

00:48:29.030 --> 00:48:30.600
in Brandon Carter's
model there's

00:48:30.600 --> 00:48:32.602
a hundred civilizations
that have occurred

00:48:32.602 --> 00:48:33.810
across cosmic history, right?

00:48:33.810 --> 00:48:36.960
And we now know that there--
not know-- but now the idea is

00:48:36.960 --> 00:48:38.380
there's not 10 hard steps.

00:48:38.380 --> 00:48:40.080
There's maybe only
five hard steps.

00:48:40.080 --> 00:48:43.157
Now again this is all
still controversial.

00:48:43.157 --> 00:48:45.240
